  <sections xmi:id="_Gkbf4DerEdyrF6K2SkiByg" name="The criteria used to evaluate reference architectures has been approved by the stakeholders." guid="_Gkbf4DerEdyrF6K2SkiByg"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_H3bY0DerEdyrF6K2SkiByg" name="All major requirement areas have been considered." guid="_H3bY0DerEdyrF6K2SkiByg"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_JgVQUDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg" name="The reference architecture can meet the critical dependencies in the target environment." guid="_JgVQUDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This includes the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The deployment of the architecture at all locations.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The integration of other existing (and planned) systems into the chosen architecture.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &amp;nbsp;Performance, security and scalability requirements.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_VWp-EDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg" name="Tradeoffs have been validated between the stakeholders and asset providers." guid="_VWp-EDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        They meet business objectives for the system.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        They sufficiently mitigate against risk.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        They do not compromise the use of assets.&amp;nbsp; For example the assets are available within the published time&#xD;
        scales, there are suitable service agreements in place etc.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_foFxoDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg" name="The architecture is resilient to anticipated changes." guid="_foFxoDerEdyrF6K2SkiByg"/>
